	<item>
	  <title>Math Test</title>
	  <link>//Math-Test</link>
	  <author>DigiBits</author>
	  <pubDate>2016-04-02T15:48:00+05:30</pubDate>
	  <guid>//Math-Test</guid>
	  <description><![CDATA[
	     <p>Testing some inline math : $\psi$</p>

<p>Now a inline math with special character: $|\psi\rangle x^*$</p>

<p>Test a display math:</p>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">|\psi_1\rangle = a|0\rangle + b|1\rangle</script>

<p>Is it O.K.?</p>

<p>Test a display math with equation number:</p>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{equation}
   |\psi_1\rangle = a|0\rangle + b|1\rangle
\end{equation}</script>

<p>Is it O.K.?</p>

<p>Test a display math with equation number:</p>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">% <![CDATA[
\begin{align}
    |\psi_1\rangle &= a|0\rangle + b|1\rangle \\\\
    |\psi_2\rangle &= c|0\rangle + d|1\rangle
  \end{align} %]]></script>

<p>Is it O.K.?</p>

<p>And test a display math without equaltion number:</p>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">% <![CDATA[
\begin{align*}
    |\psi_1\rangle &= a|0\rangle + b|1\rangle \\\\
    |\psi_2\rangle &= c|0\rangle + d|1\rangle
  \end{align*} %]]></script>

<p>Is it O.K.?</p>

<p>Test a display math with equation number:</p>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">% <![CDATA[
\begin{align}
      |\psi_1\rangle &= a|0\rangle + b|1\rangle \\\\
      |\psi_2\rangle &= c|0\rangle + d|1\rangle
   \end{align} %]]></script>

<p>Is it O.K.?</p>

<p>And test a display math without equaltion number:</p>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">% <![CDATA[
\begin{align*}
        |\psi_1\rangle &= a|0\rangle + b|1\rangle \\\\
        |\psi_2\rangle &= c|0\rangle + d|1\rangle
    \end{align*} %]]></script>

<p>Is it O.K.?</p>

<p>Kramdown exaple Math:</p>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">% <![CDATA[
\begin{align*}
  & \phi(x,y) = \phi \left(\sum_{i=1}^n x_ie_i, \sum_{j=1}^n y_je_j \right)
  = \sum_{i=1}^n \sum_{j=1}^n x_i y_j \phi(e_i, e_j) = \\
  & (x_1, \ldots, x_n) \left( \begin{array}{ccc}
      \phi(e_1, e_1) & \cdots & \phi(e_1, e_n) \\
      \vdots & \ddots & \vdots \\
      \phi(e_n, e_1) & \cdots & \phi(e_n, e_n)
    \end{array} \right)
  \left( \begin{array}{c}
      y_1 \\
      \vdots \\
      y_n
    \end{array} \right)
\end{align*} %]]></script>

	  ]]></description>
